***************************************************************

Description: Catches private messages (when you're away) and nick highlights in irssi and directs them to the Prowl API.
http://prowlapp.com/

Version: 0.2

Author: Nathan Chowning (nathanchowning@me.com)

######
# This script is based on fnotify created by Thorsten Leemhuis
# http://www.leemhuis.info/files/fnotify/
######

           ___  ___                              
          |   |/   \___________     ____   ____  
          |   |    /  ___/\__  \   / ___\_/ __ \ 
          |       /\___ \  / __ \_/ /_/  >  ___/ 
          |______//____  >(____  /\___  / \___  >
                       \/      \//_____/      \/ 

***************************************************************

This script requires the following perl modules:
Crypt::SSLeay
WebService::Prowl

On most setups you should be able to just run "cpan WebService::Prowl"
In some cases it might require a little more work.

You'll need to edit the script to add your Prowl API key (replace "PUT_API_KEY_HERE" with your API key).

To load this script, simply put it in your ~/.irssi/scripts/ directory and do:
/script load irssi-prowl-notifier.pl
